Definition: contrary to conscience or morality or law
Example: it is wrong for the rich to take advantage of the poor; cheating is wrong; it is wrong to lie
Synonyms: noun, attribute, wrong, act, wrongness, RIGHT, EVIL, IMPROPER, IMMORAL, UNETHICAL, UNJUST, WICKED, rightness, contrary, to, conscience, or, morality, law, it, is, for, the, rich, take, advantage, of, poor, cheating, lie
Category: adj.all
